People don't understand how mythologically fertile the Soviet cityscape truly was - in every town it gave birth to dozens of local urban legends, rumours, sightings.

Stories of cannibalism, of large mysterious strangers, people disappearing, lights in the sky, cults, creatures.

One of the ones that have stuck with me the most is a tale about some neighbourhood being terrorized by a large black dog that seemingly appeared and disappeared out of nowhere. A man was found in a staircase, brutalized to death, chewed up by seemingly a giant beast...
